<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>The Station — Sales Analytics</title>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Playfair+Display:wght@400;600;700&family=DM+Sans:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<script src="https://cdn.plot.ly/plotly-2.35.2.min.js"></script>
<style>
/* ── Reset & Base ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */
*, *::before, *::after { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }

:root {
  --cream: #faf7f2;
  --espresso: #2c1810;
  --terracotta: #9b4a2c;
  --warm-brown: #6b3a2a;
  --sage: #7a8b6f;
  --gold: #c4953a;
  --slate: #4a5568;
  --light-border: #e8e0d8;
  --card-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(44,24,16,0.06);
  --section-gap: 48px;
}

html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }

body {
  font-family: 'DM Sans', -apple-system, sans-serif;
  background: var(--cream);
  color: var(--espresso);
  line-height: 1.6;
  -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
}

/* ── Navigation ───────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.nav {
  position: sticky;
  top: 0;
  z-index: 100;
  background: rgba(250,247,242,0.95);
  backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--light-border);
  padding: 0 24px;
}

.nav-inner {
  max-width: 1200px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 8px;
  overflow-x: auto;
  scrollbar-width: none;
  -ms-overflow-style: none;
  padding: 12px 0;
}
.nav-inner::-webkit-scrollbar { display: none; }

.nav-brand {
  font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
  font-weight: 700;
  font-size: 18px;
  white-space: nowrap;
  margin-right: 16px;
  color: var(--espresso);
  text-decoration: none;
}

.nav a:not(.nav-brand) {
  font-size: 13px;
  font-weight: 500;
  color: var(--warm-brown);
  text-decoration: none;
  white-space: nowrap;
  padding: 6px 12px;
  border-radius: 6px;
  transition: all 0.2s;
}
.nav a:not(.nav-brand):hover {
  background: rgba(155,74,44,0.08);
  color: var(--terracotta);
}

/* ── Layout ───────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.container {
  max-width: 1200px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 0 24px;
}

section {
  padding: var(--section-gap) 0;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--light-border);
}
section:last-of-type { border-bottom: none; }

/* ── Typography ───────────────────────────────────────────────── */
h1, h2, h3 { font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; }

.page-header {
  text-align: center;
  padding: 56px 0 40px;
}
.page-header h1 {
  font-size: 42px;
  font-weight: 700;
  margin-bottom: 8px;
}
.page-header .subtitle {
  font-size: 18px;
  color: var(--warm-brown);
}
.page-header .meta {
  font-size: 13px;
  color: var(--slate);
  margin-top: 12px;
}

.section-header {
  margin-bottom: 24px;
}
.section-header h2 {
  font-size: 28px;
  margin-bottom: 6px;
}
.section-header .section-desc {
  font-size: 15px;
  color: var(--warm-brown);
}

h3 {
  font-size: 20px;
  margin-bottom: 12px;
  margin-top: 24px;
}

/* ── KPI Cards ────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.kpi-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
  gap: 16px;
  margin-bottom: 32px;
}

.kpi-card {
  background: white;
  border-radius: 12px;
  padding: 24px;
  box-shadow: var(--card-shadow);
}
.kpi-card .label {
  font-size: 13px;
  font-weight: 600;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.5px;
  color: var(--slate);
  margin-bottom: 4px;
}
.kpi-card .value {
  font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
  font-size: 32px;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--terracotta);
}
.kpi-card .detail {
  font-size: 13px;
  color: var(--warm-brown);
  margin-top: 4px;
}

/* ── Chart Cards ──────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.chart-card {
  background: white;
  border-radius: 12px;
  padding: 24px;
  box-shadow: var(--card-shadow);
  margin-bottom: 24px;
}
.chart-card h3 {
  font-size: 18px;
  margin-top: 0;
  margin-bottom: 16px;
  color: var(--espresso);
}
.chart-container {
  width: 100%;
  min-height: 300px;
}

.two-col {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  gap: 24px;
}

/* ── Insight Boxes ────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.insight-box {
  background: white;
  border-radius: 12px;
  border-left: 4px solid var(--terracotta);
  padding: 20px 24px;
  margin: 20px 0;
  box-shadow: var(--card-shadow);
}
.insight-box.positive { border-left-color: var(--sage); }
.insight-box.caution { border-left-color: var(--gold); }

.insight-box h4 {
  font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
  font-size: 15px;
  font-weight: 700;
  margin-bottom: 8px;
  color: var(--espresso);
}
.insight-box p, .insight-box ul {
  font-size: 14px;
  line-height: 1.7;
  color: var(--warm-brown);
}
.insight-box ul { padding-left: 20px; }
.insight-box li { margin-bottom: 4px; }

/* ── Tables ───────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.data-table {
  width: 100%;
  border-collapse: collapse;
  font-size: 14px;
}
.data-table th {
  text-align: left;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--slate);
  font-size: 12px;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.5px;
  padding: 10px 12px;
  border-bottom: 2px solid var(--light-border);
}
.data-table td {
  padding: 10px 12px;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--light-border);
}
.data-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
.data-table .num { text-align: right; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }

/* ── Recommendation Cards ─────────────────────────────────────── */
.rec-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(320px, 1fr));
  gap: 20px;
}

.rec-card {
  background: white;
  border-radius: 12px;
  padding: 24px;
  box-shadow: var(--card-shadow);
  border-top: 4px solid var(--terracotta);
}
.rec-card .rec-num {
  font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
  font-size: 36px;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--terracotta);
  opacity: 0.3;
  float: right;
  margin-top: -8px;
}
.rec-card h4 {
  font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
  font-size: 18px;
  margin-bottom: 8px;
}
.rec-card p {
  font-size: 14px;
  color: var(--warm-brown);
  line-height: 1.7;
}
.rec-card .impact {
  display: inline-block;
  margin-top: 12px;
  font-size: 12px;
  font-weight: 600;
  padding: 4px 10px;
  border-radius: 4px;
  background: rgba(155,74,44,0.08);
  color: var(--terracotta);
}

/* ── Footer ───────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.footer {
  text-align: center;
  padding: 40px 0;
  font-size: 13px;
  color: var(--slate);
}

/* ── Responsive ───────────────────────────────────────────────── */
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .page-header h1 { font-size: 32px; }
  .page-header .subtitle { font-size: 16px; }
  .kpi-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
  .kpi-card .value { font-size: 24px; }
  .two-col { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .rec-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .section-header h2 { font-size: 24px; }
  section { padding: 32px 0; }
  .nav-brand { font-size: 16px; }
}

@media (max-width: 480px) {
  .kpi-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
}

/* ── Print ────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
@media print {
  .nav { display: none; }
  section { break-inside: avoid; padding: 24px 0; }
  .chart-card, .kpi-card, .insight-box { break-inside: avoid; }
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<!-- Navigation -->
<nav class="nav">
  <div class="nav-inner">
    <a href="#top" class="nav-brand">The Station</a>
    <a href="#summary">Summary</a>
    <a href="#revenue">Revenue</a>
    <a href="#time">Time Patterns</a>
    <a href="#menu">Menu</a>
    <a href="#weather">Weather</a>
    <a href="#tips">Tips</a>
    <a href="#staffing">Staffing</a>
    <a href="#staff">Staff</a>
    <a href="#whatif">What-If</a>
    <a href="#local">Local Intel</a>
    <a href="#recs">Recommendations</a>
  </div>
</nav>

<div class="container" id="top">

<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<!-- HEADER -->
<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="page-header">
  <h1>The Station</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">Sales Analytics Dashboard</p>
  <p class="meta">{{ stats.date_range }} &middot; {{ generated_at }}</p>
</div>

<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<!-- EXECUTIVE SUMMARY -->
<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section id="summary">
  <div class="section-header">
    <h2>Executive Summary</h2>
    <p class="section-desc">Key performance metrics since opening day</p>
  </div>

  <div class="kpi-grid">
    <div class="kpi-card">
      <div class="label">Total Revenue</div>
      <div class="value">${{ "{:,.0f}".format(stats.total_revenue) }}</div>
      <div class="detail">{{ stats.n_days }} days of operation</div>
    </div>
    <div class="kpi-card">
      <div class="label">Avg Daily Revenue</div>
      <div class="value">${{ "{:,.0f}".format(stats.avg_daily_revenue) }}</div>
      <div class="detail">{{ stats.avg_daily_orders }} orders/day</div>
    </div>
    <div class="kpi-card">
      <div class="label">Avg Order Value</div>
      <div class="value">${{ "{:.2f}".format(stats.avg_order_value) }}</div>
      <div class="detail">{{ stats.avg_items_per_order }} items/order</div>
    </div>
    <div class="kpi-card">
      <div class="label">Total Orders</div>
      <div class="value">{{ "{:,}".format(stats.total_orders) }}</div>
      <div class="detail">{{ "{:,}".format(stats.total_items_sold) }} items sold</div>
    </div>
    <div class="kpi-card">
      <div class="label">Best Day</div>
      <div class="value">${{ "{:,.0f}".format(stats.best_day_revenue) }}</div>
      <div class="detail">{{ stats.best_day_date }}</div>
    </div>
    <div class="kpi-card">
      <div class="label">Total Tips</div>
      <div class="value">${{ "{:,.0f}".format(stats.total_tips) }}</div>
      <div class="detail">{{ stats.tip_rate_pct }}% of revenue</div>
    </div>
    {% if stats.latest_weekly_growth is defined %}
    <div class="kpi-card">
      <div class="label">Latest Week Growth</div>
      <div class="value">{{ "{:+.1f}".format(stats.latest_weekly_growth) }}%</div>
      <div class="detail">Avg: {{ "{:+.1f}".format(stats.avg_weekly_growth) }}% week-over-week</div>
    </div>
    {% endif %}
    <div class="kpi-card">
      <div class="label">Top Item</div>
      <div class="value" style="font-size: 20px;">{{ stats.top_item }}</div>
      <div class="detail">${{ "{:,.0f}".format(stats.top_item_revenue) }} revenue</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  {% if stats.periods is defined %}
  <div class="insight-box caution">
    <h4>Startup Context</h4>
    <p>
      <strong>The first {{ stats.periods.rampup_days }} days were a ramp-up period</strong> — the community
      was still discovering The Station. Ramp-up averaged
      <strong>${{ "{:,.0f}".format(stats.periods.rampup_avg_revenue) }}/day</strong>
      ({{ stats.periods.rampup_avg_orders }} orders/day) vs. steady state at
      <strong>${{ "{:,.0f}".format(stats.periods.steady_avg_revenue) }}/day</strong>
      ({{ stats.periods.steady_avg_orders }} orders/day) —
      a <strong>{{ "{:+.0f}".format(stats.periods.growth_from_rampup) }}% improvement</strong>.
      {% if stats.periods.severe_weather_days > 0 %}
      Additionally, <strong>{{ stats.periods.severe_weather_days }} severe weather days</strong>
      impacted sales by ~{{ "{:.0f}".format(stats.periods.severe_impact_pct) }}%
      (${{ "{:,.0f}".format(stats.periods.severe_avg_revenue) }}/day vs.
      ${{ "{:,.0f}".format(stats.periods.normal_avg_revenue) }}/day on normal days).
      {% endif %}
      <em>Steady-state metrics below are more representative of ongoing performance than the all-time averages.</em>
    </p>
  </div>
  {% endif %}

  <div class="insight-box positive">
    <h4>State of the Station</h4>
    <p>
      In {{ stats.n_days }} days since opening, The Station has generated
      <strong>${{ "{:,.0f}".format(stats.total_revenue) }}</strong> in revenue from
      <strong>{{ "{:,}".format(stats.total_orders) }}</strong> orders.
      {% if stats.avg_weekly_growth is defined and stats.avg_weekly_growth > 0 %}
      Revenue is trending upward with an average weekly growth of {{ "{:+.1f}".format(stats.avg_weekly_growth) }}%.
      {% endif %}
      The busiest day is typically <strong>{{ stats.busiest_day }}</strong> and the
      slowest is <strong>{{ stats.slowest_day }}</strong>.
      {{ stats.card_pct }}% of transactions are card, {{ stats.cash_pct }}% cash.
      The food attach rate is <strong>{{ stats.attach.attach_rate }}%</strong>
      ({{ stats.attach.drink_plus_food }} of {{ stats.attach.drink_orders }} drink orders include food).
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<!-- REVENUE TRENDS -->
<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section id="revenue">
  <div class="section-header">
    <h2>Revenue Trends</h2>
    <p class="section-desc">Daily, weekly, and day-of-week revenue patterns</p>
  </div>

  <div class="chart-card">
    <h3>Daily Revenue</h3>
    <div class="chart-container" id="chart-daily-revenue"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="two-col">
    <div class="chart-card">
      <h3>Revenue by Day of Week</h3>
      <div class="chart-container" id="chart-dow-revenue"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="chart-card">
      <h3>Average Order Value Trend</h3>
      <div class="chart-container" id="chart-aov-trend"></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="chart-card">
    <h3>Week-over-Week Comparison</h3>
    <div class="chart-container" id="chart-wow-growth"></div>
  </div>

  {% if tables.weekly_growth %}
  <div class="chart-card">
    <h3>Weekly Revenue Summary</h3>
    <table class="data-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Week</th>
          <th class="num">Revenue</th>
          <th class="num">Growth</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {% for w in tables.weekly_growth %}
        <tr>
          <td>{{ w.week }}</td>
          <td class="num">${{ "{:,.0f}".format(w.revenue) }}</td>
          <td class="num">
            {% if w.growth_pct is not none %}
              <span style="color: {% if w.growth_pct >= 0 %}var(--sage){% else %}#c0392b{% endif %}">
                {{ "{:+.1f}".format(w.growth_pct) }}%
              </span>
            {% else %}—{% endif %}
          </td>
        </tr>
        {% endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
  {% endif %}

  <div class="insight-box">
    <h4>Revenue Insights</h4>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>{{ stats.busiest_day }}</strong> is the strongest day — consider running promotions or specials on <strong>{{ stats.slowest_day }}</strong> to balance demand.</li>
      <li>Best single day was <strong>{{ stats.best_day_date }}</strong> (${{ "{:,.0f}".format(stats.best_day_revenue) }}) — review what made that day exceptional (weather, event, promotion?).</li>
      <li>The 7-day moving average smooths out daily noise — watch for the trendline direction, not individual day spikes.</li>
      <li>Week-over-week overlay shows seasonal and growth patterns. Consistent upward movement across all days means genuine growth, not just one-off spikes.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<!-- TIME PATTERNS -->
<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section id="time">
  <div class="section-header">
    <h2>Time-of-Day Patterns</h2>
    <p class="section-desc">When customers come — and when they don't</p>
  </div>

  <div class="chart-card">
    <h3>Orders by Hour &amp; Day (Heatmap)</h3>
    <div class="chart-container" id="chart-hourly-heatmap"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="two-col">
    <div class="chart-card">
      <h3>Morning Rush Detail (6–10 AM)</h3>
      <div class="chart-container" id="chart-morning-rush"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="chart-card">
      <h3>Order Size Distribution</h3>
      <div class="chart-container" id="chart-order-size-dist"></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="insight-box">
    <h4>Time Pattern Insights</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>The heatmap reveals your true peak hours — the darkest cells are where you need the most staff and prep.</li>
      <li>Morning rush chart shows 5-minute order clusters. Train departure annotations (dashed lines) help identify commuter patterns — if you see spikes right before departures, commuters are your morning base.</li>
      <li>Dead zones (lightest cells) are opportunities: consider happy hours, afternoon specials, or social media pushes during slow periods.</li>
      <li>Most orders contain {{ stats.avg_items_per_order }} items — multi-item combos or "add a pastry" prompts could lift this.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<!-- MENU PERFORMANCE -->
<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section id="menu">
  <div class="section-header">
    <h2>Menu Performance</h2>
    <p class="section-desc">What sells, what doesn't, and what could sell better</p>
  </div>

  <div class="two-col">
    <div class="chart-card">
      <h3>Top Items by Revenue</h3>
      <div class="chart-container" id="chart-top-items-revenue"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="chart-card">
      <h3>Top Items by Quantity</h3>
      <div class="chart-container" id="chart-top-items-qty"></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="two-col">
    <div class="chart-card">
      <h3>Category Revenue Mix</h3>
      <div class="chart-container" id="chart-category-mix"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="chart-card">
      <h3>Category Trend (7-Day Avg)</h3>
      <div class="chart-container" id="chart-category-trend"></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  {% if tables.item_pairings %}
  <div class="chart-card">
    <h3>Frequently Purchased Together</h3>
    <p style="font-size: 14px; color: var(--warm-brown); margin-bottom: 16px;">
      Items most commonly appearing in the same order — natural combo candidates.
    </p>
    <table class="data-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Item A</th><th>Item B</th><th class="num">Times Together</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {% for pair in tables.item_pairings[:10] %}
        <tr>
          <td>{{ pair.item_a }}</td>
          <td>{{ pair.item_b }}</td>
          <td class="num">{{ pair.count }}</td>
        </tr>
        {% endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
  {% endif %}

  {% if tables.underperformers %}
  <div class="chart-card">
    <h3>Underperforming Items</h3>
    <p style="font-size: 14px; color: var(--warm-brown); margin-bottom: 16px;">
      Items ordered less than once per day — candidates for promotion, repositioning, or removal.
    </p>
    <table class="data-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Item</th><th class="num">Orders/Day</th><th class="num">Total Revenue</th><th class="num">Total Orders</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {% for item in tables.underperformers[:10] %}
        <tr>
          <td>{{ item.item }}</td>
          <td class="num">{{ item.orders_per_day }}</td>
          <td class="num">${{ "{:,.0f}".format(item.total_revenue) }}</td>
          <td class="num">{{ item.total_orders }}</td>
        </tr>
        {% endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
  {% endif %}

  <div class="insight-box">
    <h4>Menu Insights</h4>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Food attach rate: {{ stats.attach.attach_rate }}%</strong> — for every 100 drink orders, {{ stats.attach.drink_plus_food }} also buy food. Industry benchmarks for cafes are 30-40%. {% if stats.attach.attach_rate < 30 %}There's significant room to grow food sales through suggestive selling and combo deals.{% elif stats.attach.attach_rate < 40 %}You're in the healthy range — maintain with consistent upselling.{% else %}This is above industry average — your food program is working well.{% endif %}</li>
      <li>Items that appear together frequently are natural combo candidates. Consider bundling the top pairs at a slight discount to increase perceived value and AOV.</li>
      <li>Underperformers ordered less than 1x/day deserve attention: either promote them (signage, staff suggestion, social media) or replace them with something from the top sellers' category.</li>
      <li>Watch the category trend chart — if a category is declining week over week, investigate freshness, variety, or seasonal relevance.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<!-- WEATHER IMPACT -->
<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section id="weather">
  <div class="section-header">
    <h2>Weather Impact</h2>
    <p class="section-desc">How Tuxedo Park weather drives (or dampens) sales</p>
  </div>

  <div class="chart-card">
    <h3>Temperature &amp; Precipitation vs. Revenue</h3>
    <div class="chart-container" id="chart-weather-correlation"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="kpi-grid">
    <div class="kpi-card">
      <div class="label">Rainy Day Avg Revenue</div>
      <div class="value">${{ "{:,.0f}".format(stats.weather.avg_revenue_rainy) }}</div>
      <div class="detail">{{ stats.weather.rainy_days }} rainy days</div>
    </div>
    <div class="kpi-card">
      <div class="label">Dry Day Avg Revenue</div>
